        <abstract> 
<p>He is delivering address at the British Medical Association’s Manchester meeting ["Address in medicine", <hi rend="italic">Br. Med. J.</hi> (1877) pt 2: 168–73]. Will develop theme that parasites are variations of common types, e.g., <hi rend="italic">Bacillus anthracis</hi> is a variant of <hi rend="italic">B. subtilis</hi>. Asks for more examples.</p> 
        </abstract>
